1089
01:25:43,662 --> 01:25:44,580
Hey, Wallace.

1090
01:25:44,747 --> 01:25:45,998
Take a look at this.

1091
01:25:51,670 --> 01:25:52,503
Fifield?

1092
01:25:55,175 --> 01:25:57,135
What the hell is going on down there?

1093
01:26:11,023 --> 01:26:12,149
I'm coming down there.

1094
01:26:12,316 --> 01:26:13,616
Chance, you're suiting up.

1095
01:26:13,735 --> 01:26:15,585
- Come on.
- Don't let it on the ship!

1096
01:26:30,502 --> 01:26:31,335
Take him out!

1097
01:26:31,836 --> 01:26:32,669
Got him!

1098
01:26:34,714 --> 01:26:35,547
Do it!

1099
01:26:39,218 --> 01:26:41,346
- You ready, Chance?
- Yes.

1100
01:26:44,348 --> 01:26:45,182
Come on!

1101
01:26:45,391 --> 01:26:46,559
Get in the rover!

1102
01:26:47,476 --> 01:26:48,727
We gotta get out of here!

1103
01:26:55,901 --> 01:26:56,735
Go!

1104
01:27:28,266 --> 01:27:29,559
What is that?

1105
01:28:04,970 --> 01:28:07,138
You've been asleep.

1106
01:28:07,306 --> 01:28:09,975
You were on the ship all this time. Why?

1107
01:28:11,435 --> 01:28:12,894
Well, l...

1108
01:28:13,061 --> 01:28:14,939
l have a few days of life left in me.

1109
01:28:16,148 --> 01:28:17,525
I didn't wanna waste them...

1110
01:28:17,608 --> 01:28:19,818
...until you could deliver
what you promised.

1111
01:28:21,027 --> 01:28:22,571
To meet my maker.

1112
01:28:22,737 --> 01:28:23,947
There we are, sir.

1113
01:28:24,155 --> 01:28:27,326
- Nice and clean.
- Haven't you told him they're all gone?

1114
01:28:28,910 --> 01:28:32,080
But they're not all gone, Dr. Shaw.

1115
01:28:32,330 --> 01:28:33,999
One of them is still alive.

1116
01:28:34,750 --> 01:28:36,627
We're on our way to see him now.

1117
01:28:36,919 --> 01:28:38,003
What?

1118
01:28:38,378 --> 01:28:39,671
Turn me around.

1119
01:28:40,380 --> 01:28:45,177
You convinced me that...

1120
01:28:46,720 --> 01:28:48,889
...if these things made us...

1121
01:28:50,140 --> 01:28:52,684
...then surely they could save us.

1122
01:28:53,351 --> 01:28:54,311
My stick, please.

1123
01:28:59,024 --> 01:29:01,234
Well, save me, anyway.

1124
01:29:01,734 --> 01:29:03,736
Save you from what?

1125
01:29:04,362 --> 01:29:05,821
Death, of course.

1126
01:29:06,113 --> 01:29:07,197
Stand me up.

1127
01:29:11,661 --> 01:29:12,662
I'm all right.

1128
01:29:13,496 --> 01:29:14,663
I'm all right.

1129
01:29:15,664 --> 01:29:16,832
Yes, sir.

1130
01:29:17,082 --> 01:29:18,332
But you don't understand.

1131
01:29:19,042 --> 01:29:20,377
You don't know.

1132
01:29:20,544 --> 01:29:23,339
This place isn't what we thought it was.
They aren't...

1133
01:29:23,506 --> 01:29:25,549
...what we thought they were.

1134
01:29:25,716 --> 01:29:26,884
I was wrong.

1135
01:29:27,050 --> 01:29:28,303
We were so wrong.

1136
01:29:28,845 --> 01:29:30,263
Charlie...

1137
01:29:30,888 --> 01:29:33,057
Dr. Holloway's dead.

1138
01:29:34,392 --> 01:29:36,394
We must leave!

1139
01:29:36,895 --> 01:29:38,855
And what would Charlie do...

1140
01:29:39,147 --> 01:29:44,026
...now that we're so close...

1141
01:29:44,318 --> 01:29:47,697
...to answering
the most meaningful questions...

1142
01:29:47,864 --> 01:29:49,407
...ever asked by mankind?

1143
01:29:50,783 --> 01:29:52,493
How can you leave without...

1144
01:29:52,701 --> 01:29:54,662
...knowing what they are?

1145
01:30:01,670 --> 01:30:03,713
Or have you lost your faith, Shaw?

1146
01:30:39,831 --> 01:30:42,585
Okay. Okay.

1147
01:31:01,937 --> 01:31:03,314
Come in.

1148
01:31:10,488 --> 01:31:12,489
Where the hell are you going, doc?

1149
01:31:12,823 --> 01:31:14,825
You know what this place is?

1150
01:31:15,242 --> 01:31:18,954
Those Engineers? This ain't their home.

1151
01:31:20,371 --> 01:31:22,791
It's an installation.
Maybe even military.

1152
01:31:23,333 --> 01:31:26,128
They put it out here
because they're not stupid enough...

1153
01:31:26,211 --> 01:31:29,464
...to make weapons of mass destruction
on their own doorstep.

1154
01:31:30,131 --> 01:31:33,676
That's what all that shit is
in those vases.

1155
01:31:34,093 --> 01:31:35,262
They made it here.

1156
01:31:35,512 --> 01:31:39,557
It got out, it turned on them. The end.

1157
01:31:41,560 --> 01:31:43,645
It's time for us to go home.

1158
01:31:44,187 --> 01:31:46,022
One of them is still alive.

1159
01:31:50,611 --> 01:31:53,155
Don't you want to know
what they have to say?

1160
01:31:56,616 --> 01:31:58,284
I don't care.

1161
01:32:00,203 --> 01:32:01,330
Right.

1162
01:32:02,122 --> 01:32:04,040
All you do is fly the ship.

1163
01:32:04,374 --> 01:32:05,542
That's right.

1164
01:32:05,708 --> 01:32:09,338
But you must care
about something, captain.

1165
01:32:11,673 --> 01:32:14,426
If you didn't, why are you here?

1166
01:32:17,387 --> 01:32:18,889
How about this?

1167
01:32:20,849 --> 01:32:23,143
No matter what happens down there...

1168
01:32:24,435 --> 01:32:26,980
...l can't bring none of that shit
back home with us.

1169
01:32:27,063 --> 01:32:28,357
Can't let it happen.

1170
01:32:29,858 --> 01:32:31,308
L'll do whatever l have to...

1171
01:32:31,443 --> 01:32:33,152
...to see that it doesn't.

1172
01:32:35,030 --> 01:32:36,531
Make sure you do, captain.

1173
01:32:52,088 --> 01:32:54,215
So you came after all.

1174
01:32:54,508 --> 01:32:56,051
I thought you wanted me to.

1175
01:32:56,343 --> 01:32:58,929
After all your attempts
to stop me from coming here...

1176
01:32:59,012 --> 01:33:00,430
...l'm surprised to see you.

1177
01:33:01,181 --> 01:33:02,431
It's all right. Leave us.

1178
01:33:02,975 --> 01:33:04,393
Yes, sir.

1179
01:33:16,446 --> 01:33:17,113
If you're...

1180
01:33:17,322 --> 01:33:19,022
...going down there, you will die.

1181
01:33:22,077 --> 01:33:24,027
Very negative way of looking at things.

1182
01:33:26,122 --> 01:33:28,572
That's exactly why
you should have stayed at home.

1183
01:33:28,958 --> 01:33:32,045
Did you really think l was gonna
sit in a boardroom for years...

1184
01:33:32,128 --> 01:33:33,879
...arguing over who was in charge...

1185
01:33:33,962 --> 01:33:37,300
...while you go look for some miracle
on some...

1186
01:33:37,467 --> 01:33:41,137
...godforsaken rock
in the middle of space?

1187
01:33:44,056 --> 01:33:45,807
A king has...

1188
01:33:45,932 --> 01:33:48,519
...his reign, and then he dies.

1189
01:33:49,395 --> 01:33:50,771
It's inevitable.

1190
01:33:53,273 --> 01:33:54,609
That...

1191
01:33:55,318 --> 01:33:57,320
...is the natural order of things.

1192
01:34:10,165 --> 01:34:11,542
Anything else?

1193
01:34:13,418 --> 01:34:14,795
No...

1194
01:34:16,088 --> 01:34:17,673
...Father.

1195
01:34:19,258 --> 01:34:20,133
That's it.

1196
01:34:33,189 --> 01:34:34,839
I didn't think you had it in you.

1197
01:34:35,691 --> 01:34:36,317
Sorry.

1198
01:34:36,483 --> 01:34:38,860
Poor choice of words.

1199
01:34:40,153 --> 01:34:43,449
Extraordinary survival instincts,
Elizabeth.

1200
01:34:48,454 --> 01:34:50,204
What happens when Weyland is not...

1201
01:34:50,289 --> 01:34:51,540
...around to program you?

1202
01:34:52,583 --> 01:34:54,209
I suppose l'll be free.

1203
01:34:55,128 --> 01:34:56,462
You want that?

1204
01:34:56,629 --> 01:34:58,172
"Want"?

1205
01:34:58,339 --> 01:35:00,216
Not a concept l'm familiar with.

1206
01:35:00,508 --> 01:35:02,051
That being said...

1207
01:35:03,093 --> 01:35:05,243
...doesn't everyone
want their parents dead?

1208
01:35:07,139 --> 01:35:08,182
I didn't.

1209
01:35:09,350 --> 01:35:10,183
Dr. Shaw.

1210
01:35:11,810 --> 01:35:13,260
So pleased you could join us.

1211
01:35:28,035 --> 01:35:30,246
You can take your helmet off
if you like, sir.

1212
01:35:30,329 --> 01:35:31,162
What?

1213
01:35:31,246 --> 01:35:33,749
The air is perfectly breathable.

1214
01:35:33,915 --> 01:35:35,084
Are you sure?

1215
01:35:35,251 --> 01:35:36,252
Positive.

1216
01:35:36,794 --> 01:35:41,548
Wait. We still don't know how
Holloway got infected. lf it's in the air.

1217
01:35:42,132 --> 01:35:43,550
It's not.

1218
01:35:43,842 --> 01:35:45,593
How do you know that?

1219
01:35:45,885 --> 01:35:46,886
Smells fine to me.

1220
01:35:49,556 --> 01:35:50,932
- Shall we?
- Please.

1221
01:35:56,437 --> 01:35:58,189
The bridge is just up ahead.

1222
01:35:58,356 --> 01:35:59,440
What is this?

1223
01:36:00,608 --> 01:36:02,444
It's a cargo hold.

1224
01:36:11,494 --> 01:36:14,122
Janek? Are you seeing this?

1225
01:36:15,416 --> 01:36:16,625
How many is there, Shaw?

1226
01:36:16,792 --> 01:36:17,625
Thousands.

1227
01:36:18,960 --> 01:36:20,837
What the hell?

1228
01:36:24,674 --> 01:36:26,592
Ravel, give me those schematics.

1229
01:36:29,471 --> 01:36:31,598
Putting it on the table now.

1230
01:36:32,974 --> 01:36:33,975
Strip away the dome.

1231
01:36:34,600 --> 01:36:37,395
Isolate that area, bring it up.

1232
01:36:37,562 --> 01:36:39,189
Bringing it up, captain.

1233
01:36:42,276 --> 01:36:43,360
Enlarge that.

1234
01:36:45,487 --> 01:36:46,821
Rotate it.

1235
01:36:50,908 --> 01:36:52,451
That is a ship.

1236
01:36:53,411 --> 01:36:54,955
Jesus Christ.

1237
01:36:56,915 --> 01:36:58,958
It's a goddamn ship.

1238
01:37:02,129 --> 01:37:04,839
A superior species, no doubt.

1239
01:37:07,133 --> 01:37:09,678
Their hypersleep chambers...

1240
01:37:09,845 --> 01:37:12,556
...will impress, l trust.

1241
01:37:21,522 --> 01:37:22,190
So they...

1242
01:37:22,357 --> 01:37:26,152
- ...were traveling somewhere.
- L've managed to work out the broad strokes.

1243
01:37:26,319 --> 01:37:29,197
It's fairly evident
they were in the process of leaving...

1244
01:37:31,158 --> 01:37:33,326
...before things went to pot.

1245
01:37:33,618 --> 01:37:34,995
Leaving to go where?

1246
01:37:36,872 --> 01:37:37,705
Earth.

1247
01:37:38,874 --> 01:37:39,707
Why?

1248
01:37:40,750 --> 01:37:42,752
Sometimes to create...

1249
01:37:43,086 --> 01:37:44,837
...one must first destroy.

1250
01:37:47,048 --> 01:37:48,383
Where is he, David?

1251
01:37:49,676 --> 01:37:50,719
This way, sir.

1252
01:37:57,141 --> 01:37:58,559
Are you sure he's alive?

1253
01:38:00,352 --> 01:38:01,395
Absolutely.

1254
01:38:05,858 --> 01:38:07,276
And you can speak to him?

1255
01:38:07,568 --> 01:38:09,069
I believe l can.

1256
01:38:45,355 --> 01:38:46,940
I'm all right, l'm all right.

1257
01:38:48,776 --> 01:38:50,027
Speak to him, David.

1258
01:38:51,362 --> 01:38:53,212
Tell him we came, just like he asked.

1259
01:38:53,322 --> 01:38:54,472
Ask where they're from.

1260
01:38:55,074 --> 01:38:56,024
What are you doing?

1261
01:38:56,117 --> 01:38:57,785
Ask him what's in his cargo.

1262
01:38:57,952 --> 01:38:58,870
It killed his people.

1263
01:38:58,953 --> 01:39:00,079
Shaw, enough.

1264
01:39:00,371 --> 01:39:02,122
- David.
- You made it here...

1265
01:39:02,623 --> 01:39:05,292
...and it was meant for us. Why?

1266
01:39:05,459 --> 01:39:07,294
Enough. For God's sake, shut her up.

1267
01:39:09,463 --> 01:39:10,547
I need to know why!

1268
01:39:10,756 --> 01:39:12,506
What did we do wrong? Why do you...

1269
01:39:12,674 --> 01:39:14,176
- ...hate us?
- She opens her...

1270
01:39:14,259 --> 01:39:15,387
...mouth again, shoot her.

1271
01:39:15,470 --> 01:39:17,388
David, continue. Tell him why l came.

1272
01:39:38,283 --> 01:39:39,116
No!

1273
01:39:45,166 --> 01:39:46,166
Ford! Move!

1274
01:40:05,310 --> 01:40:09,064
There's nothing.

1275
01:40:14,193 --> 01:40:15,988
I know.

1276
01:40:16,697 --> 01:40:19,658
Have a good journey, Mr. Weyland.

1277
01:40:26,122 --> 01:40:27,706
Time to go home.

1278
01:40:41,137 --> 01:40:44,224
Mr. Chance, take us home.

1279
01:41:57,255 --> 01:41:58,131
Oh, no!

1280
01:42:05,972 --> 01:42:06,973
Hey, cap.

1281
01:42:07,515 --> 01:42:08,665
What the hell was that?

1282
01:42:52,851 --> 01:42:53,684
Prometheus!

1283
01:42:54,144 --> 01:42:55,187
Come in!

1284
01:42:56,022 --> 01:42:57,273
Shaw, is that you?

1285
01:42:57,440 --> 01:42:58,273
Copy.

1286
01:42:58,357 --> 01:42:59,024
Janek...

1287
01:42:59,191 --> 01:43:00,192
...listen to me.

1288
01:43:01,110 --> 01:43:02,361
This ship is taking off!

1289
01:43:02,528 --> 01:43:04,238
- What?
- What is she talking about?

1290
01:43:04,321 --> 01:43:05,906
You can't let it leave!

1291
01:43:06,156 --> 01:43:07,198
You have to stop it!

1292
01:43:07,532 --> 01:43:10,160
We're not stopping anything, Shaw.
We're going home.

1293
01:43:10,661 --> 01:43:12,704
Janek, if you don't stop it...

1294
01:43:12,871 --> 01:43:14,921
...there won't be any home to go back to.

1295
01:43:16,709 --> 01:43:19,336
It's carrying death, and
it's headed for Earth.

1296
01:43:19,628 --> 01:43:22,005
- Shaw, this is not a warship.
- L know.

1297
01:43:22,214 --> 01:43:23,047
Let's go.

1298
01:43:23,174 --> 01:43:24,383
I know that.

1299
01:43:25,051 --> 01:43:26,844
But you must do it.

1300
01:43:27,386 --> 01:43:29,054
Captain, let's go!

1301
01:43:29,263 --> 01:43:31,306
Janek, please believe me! Please!

1302
01:43:46,989 --> 01:43:49,409
I told you to get this ship going.

1303
01:43:49,617 --> 01:43:50,450
Mr. Ravel.

1304
01:43:50,576 --> 01:43:51,926
Warm up the ion propulsion.

1305
01:43:52,244 --> 01:43:53,994
- What are you talking about?
- Sir.

1306
01:43:54,079 --> 01:43:55,748
Burning ion in the atmosphere...

1307
01:43:55,914 --> 01:43:59,084
- Turns us into a bullet. That's the point.
- What are you doing?

1308
01:43:59,167 --> 01:44:00,919
This is my ship. l'm telling you...

1309
01:44:01,086 --> 01:44:02,170
...to take us home!

1310
01:44:02,338 --> 01:44:03,923
Vickers, l'll eject your module onto...

1311
01:44:04,006 --> 01:44:05,757
...that surface. Two years of life.

1312
01:44:05,966 --> 01:44:08,016
You want it, or you want to stay with me?

1313
01:44:08,843 --> 01:44:10,243
You got 40 seconds to get...

1314
01:44:10,346 --> 01:44:11,396
...to the escape pod.

1315
01:44:11,514 --> 01:44:12,598
You're crazy.

1316
01:44:12,765 --> 01:44:13,598
Gentlemen...

1317
01:44:14,141 --> 01:44:15,768
...l can handle this myself.

1318
01:44:16,269 --> 01:44:17,979
Feel free to join Miss Vickers.

1319
01:44:18,896 --> 01:44:20,272
All due respect, captain.

1320
01:44:20,439 --> 01:44:23,739
You're a shit pilot and you're gonna
need all the help you can get.

1321
01:44:39,957 --> 01:44:44,129
Well, if you can't be
with the one you love

1322
01:44:44,296 --> 01:44:46,506
lf you think this means the bet's off...

1323
01:44:47,882 --> 01:44:49,133
...you're wrong.

1324
01:44:50,801 --> 01:44:53,137
Why don't you pay me on the other side?

1325
01:44:53,304 --> 01:44:55,389
All right, get us as close as we can.

1326
01:44:55,556 --> 01:44:57,475
Only got one shot at this.

1327
01:45:10,572 --> 01:45:11,405
Lifeboats away!

1328
01:45:16,494 --> 01:45:17,453
Twenty seconds...

1329
01:45:17,620 --> 01:45:18,621
...to evacuate.

1330
01:45:26,504 --> 01:45:28,381
- Countdown initiated.
- Lon propulsion...

1331
01:45:28,464 --> 01:45:29,297
...is online.

1332
01:45:29,549 --> 01:45:30,382
Ten.

1333
01:45:30,675 --> 01:45:31,508
Nine.

1334
01:45:31,634 --> 01:45:32,510
Come on!

1335
01:45:32,677 --> 01:45:33,678
Eight.

1336
01:45:45,940 --> 01:45:47,274
- Three.
- Let's do this.

1337
01:45:47,441 --> 01:45:48,317
Two.

1338
01:45:51,654 --> 01:45:52,530
Impact imminent.

1339
01:45:52,697 --> 01:45:54,115
Hands off!

1340
01:46:30,986 --> 01:46:31,819
Oh, God.

1341
01:47:19,283 --> 01:47:20,284
No. No.

1342
01:47:20,492 --> 01:47:21,535
No! No! No!

1343
01:47:37,801 --> 01:47:38,885
Oh, God.

1344
01:47:55,319 --> 01:47:58,613
Warning: You have two minutes
of oxygen remaining.

1345
01:48:47,037 --> 01:48:50,874
Warning: You have 30 seconds
of oxygen remaining.

1346
01:49:04,470 --> 01:49:05,596
Airlock sealed.

1347
01:49:07,223 --> 01:49:09,726
Oxygen levels now stabilizing.

1348
01:50:27,678 --> 01:50:29,638
Elizabeth, are you there?

1349
01:50:30,140 --> 01:50:31,349
This is David.

1350
01:50:32,559 --> 01:50:35,061
Yeah. Yeah. Yeah, l'm here.

1351
01:50:35,353 --> 01:50:37,647
You need to get out immediately.

1352
01:50:37,980 --> 01:50:39,815
He's coming for you.

1353
01:50:40,065 --> 01:50:41,108
Who's coming?

1354
01:50:41,650 --> 01:50:42,776
Airlock breach.

1355
01:50:51,369 --> 01:50:52,412
Die!

1356
01:52:17,955 --> 01:52:20,416
I'm so sorry.

1357
01:52:21,917 --> 01:52:23,752
Oh, God.

1358
01:52:24,377 --> 01:52:25,754
I'm sorry.

1359
01:52:25,962 --> 01:52:29,382
I'm sorry, Charlie, l can't do it.

1360
01:52:29,549 --> 01:52:32,719
I can't do it anymore.

1361
01:52:36,139 --> 01:52:37,599
Elizabeth.

1362
01:52:39,560 --> 01:52:40,769
Are you there?

1363
01:52:45,316 --> 01:52:46,775
Dr. Shaw...

1364
01:52:47,484 --> 01:52:48,777
...can you hear me?

1365
01:52:50,070 --> 01:52:51,321
Yes.

1366
01:52:52,781 --> 01:52:54,949
Yes, l can hear you.

1367
01:52:55,491 --> 01:52:57,369
I was afraid you were dead.

1368
01:52:59,121 --> 01:53:02,082
You have no idea what afraid is.

1369
01:53:02,916 --> 01:53:05,711
I know we've had our differences...

1370
01:53:07,129 --> 01:53:08,588
...but, please...

1371
01:53:09,506 --> 01:53:11,801
...l need to ask you for your help.

1372
01:53:11,967 --> 01:53:14,511
Why the hell would l help you?

1373
01:53:16,263 --> 01:53:20,141
Because, without me,
you'll never leave this place.

1374
01:53:20,850 --> 01:53:23,979
Neither one of us is leaving this place.

1375
01:53:24,438 --> 01:53:26,481
It's not the only ship.

1376
01:53:28,358 --> 01:53:30,443
There are many others.

1377
01:53:31,819 --> 01:53:33,154
I can operate them.

1378
01:53:42,330 --> 01:53:43,748
Dr. Shaw?

1379
01:53:56,552 --> 01:53:57,762
Dr. Shaw!

1380
01:53:59,180 --> 01:54:00,348
Over here.

1381
01:54:06,062 --> 01:54:08,022
Where is my cross?

1382
01:54:08,523 --> 01:54:10,399
The pouch in my utility belt.

1383
01:54:29,168 --> 01:54:30,962
Even after all this...

1384
01:54:31,212 --> 01:54:33,214
...you still believe, don't you?

1385
01:54:34,048 --> 01:54:37,051
You said you could
understand their navigation...

1386
01:54:37,593 --> 01:54:38,844
...use their maps.

1387
01:54:40,846 --> 01:54:42,556
Yes, of course.

1388
01:54:42,723 --> 01:54:45,059
Once we get to one of their other ships...

1389
01:54:45,226 --> 01:54:48,376
...finding a path to Earth
should be relatively straightforward.

1390
01:54:49,063 --> 01:54:52,025
I don't want to go back
to where we came from.

1391
01:54:53,860 --> 01:54:56,529
I want to go where they came from.

1392
01:54:57,906 --> 01:55:00,325
Do you think you can do that, David?

1393
01:55:04,203 --> 01:55:05,412
Yes.

1394
01:55:06,038 --> 01:55:07,915
I believe l can.

1395
01:55:17,258 --> 01:55:19,886
May l ask what you hope to achieve
by going there?

1396
01:55:20,553 --> 01:55:22,638
They created us.

1397
01:55:22,847 --> 01:55:24,391
Then they tried to kill us.

1398
01:55:24,933 --> 01:55:26,851
They changed their minds.

1399
01:55:28,436 --> 01:55:30,062
I deserve to know why.

1400
01:55:32,314 --> 01:55:33,899
The answer is irrelevant.

1401
01:55:34,942 --> 01:55:37,236
Does it matter why
they changed their minds?

1402
01:55:37,945 --> 01:55:39,113
Yes.

1403
01:55:40,448 --> 01:55:42,116
Yes, it does.

1404
01:55:43,117 --> 01:55:44,284
I don't understand.

1405
01:55:45,786 --> 01:55:46,912
Well...

1406
01:55:48,955 --> 01:55:52,000
...l guess that's because
l'm a human being...

1407
01:55:52,167 --> 01:55:53,669
...and you're a robot.

1408
01:56:03,469 --> 01:56:04,429
I'm sorry.

1409
01:56:04,596 --> 01:56:05,764
It's quite all right.

1410
01:56:20,988 --> 01:56:23,782
Final report of the vessel Prometheus.

1411
01:56:23,949 --> 01:56:24,908
The ship and her...

1412
01:56:25,075 --> 01:56:27,201
...entire crew are gone.

1413
01:56:27,410 --> 01:56:29,370
If you're receiving this transmission...

1414
01:56:29,453 --> 01:56:32,832
...make no attempt
to come to its point of origin.

1415
01:56:32,999 --> 01:56:37,212
There is only death here now,
and l'm leaving it behind.

1416
01:56:38,297 --> 01:56:40,090
It is New Year's Day...

1417
01:56:40,257 --> 01:56:43,301
...the year of our Lord, 2094.

1418
01:56:44,220 --> 01:56:46,722
My name is Elizabeth Shaw...

1419
01:56:46,930 --> 01:56:49,850
...the last survivor of the Prometheus.

1420
01:56:50,350 --> 01:56:52,852
And l am still searching.

